after-white-space;"><div>Kia ora,</div><div><br></div><div>Thank you for =
your response and for the documents provided. Having reviewed the =
material so far, it still appears incomplete and not up to date. Could =
you please:</div><div><br></div><div>1) ETA for full =
disclosure</div><div>Provide an ETA for when the full file will be =
shared, including all material identified in your =E2=80=9Centerprise-wide=
 search.=E2=80=9D If rolling disclosure is being used, please confirm =
what further releases I should expect and by =
when.</div><div><br></div><div>2) Fees</div><div>Please confirm that no =
fees will be charged for this request. If Tower intends to impose fees, =
please provide a written bill/estimate in advance detailing the =
calculation (time, hourly rate, and scope of work). Given this request =
arises from Tower=E2=80=99s own system handling and relates to my =
personal information, I consider fees =
inappropriate.</div><div><br></div><div>By way of reassurance, I am a =
professional in IT and experienced with insurance systems. I would be =
happy to review the search approach to ensure the search is both =
appropriate and efficient, and to avoid unnecessary duplication or =
administrative burden.</div><div><br></div><div>3) =
Redactions</div><div>Redactions to date appear to extend beyond simple =
removal of other people=E2=80=99s names and personal identifiers. Please =
confirm the specific legal grounds relied upon for each redaction or =
withholding, and explain why partial release was not reasonably =
practicable. Where =E2=80=9Ccommercial sensitivity=E2=80=9D is claimed, =
I ask that non-sensitive technical content and valuation inputs (scope =
descriptions, quantities, allowances, rates, contingencies) still be =
disclosed, as these are required for transparency and fairness in =
assessing my claim.</div><div><br></div><div>Ng=C4=81 =
mihi,</div><div>Raffaella</div><div><div class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" =
style=3D"direction: ltr;"><br><blockquote type=3D"cite"><div>On 25 Sep =
